{"title_page": "Wak Chan K\u02bcawiil", "text_new": "{{Infobox royalty\n| name =Wak Chan K\u02bcawiil\n| title =Ajaw of [[Tikal]]<br>21st in the line\n| image =Wak Chan K'awiil.svg\n| image_size =240px\n| caption =Wak Chan K\u02bcawiil's glyph\n| reign =December 27, 537?\u2013{{circa}} 562\n| coronation =\n| full name = \n| predecessor =[[Bird Claw]]\n| successor =[[Animal Skull]]\n| spouse  =\n| issue =\n| royal house =\n| father =[[Chak Tok Ich\u02bcaak II]]\n| mother =Lady Hand\n| birth_date =January 508?\n| birth_place =\n| death_date = {{circa}} 562\n| death_place =\n| date of burial =\n| place of burial =\n| religion =[[Maya religion]] \n|\n}}\n\n'''Wak Chan K\u02bcawiil''',<ref group=\"N\">The ruler's name, when transcribed is '''WAK-CHAN K\u02bcAWI\ua789L YAX-E\ua789B-XO\ua789K?[K\u02bcINICH AJAW]-wa''', Martin & Grube 2008, p.39.</ref> also known as '''Double Bird''' (January 508? \u2013 {{circa|562}}), was an ''[[ajaw]]'' of the [[Maya civilization|Maya]] city of [[Tikal]]. He took the throne on December 27, 537(?) and reigning probably until his death.<ref group=\"N\">These are the dates indicated on the Maya inscriptions in [[Mesoamerican Long Count calendar]], Accession: 9.5.3.9.15 12 Men 18 K\u02bcank\u02bcin, Martin & Grube 2008, p.39.</ref> He was son of [[Chak Tok Ich\u02bcaak II]] and Lady Hand. He sponsored accession of [[Yajaw Te\u02bc K\u02bcinich II]], ruler of Caracol in 553. The monument associated with Wak Chan K\u02bcawiil is Stelae 17.<ref>Martin & Grube 2008, p.39.</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=\"N\"}}\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin|indent=yes}}<!--BEGIN biblio format. If indent param. is used,  Pls use a colon (:) instead of asterisk (*) for bullet markers in the references list -->\n:{{cite book|author=Martin, Simon|authorlink=Simon Martin (Mayanist)|author2=[[Nikolai Grube]]|year=2008|title=Chronicle of the Maya Kings and Queens: Deciphering the Dynasties of the Ancient Maya|location=London and New 