onal Football League]]<ref name=\":0\" /><br />\n{{offensive-lineman-1950s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American football center}}\n{{BLP sources|date=January 2015}}\n{{No footnotes|date=January 2015}}\n{{for|the baseball player|Billy Bryan (baseball)}}\n{{Infobox gridiron football person\n| image = ||\n| caption = \n| status = Retired\n| ImageWidth = \n| number = 64, 72\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1955|6|21|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Burlington, North Carolina]]\n| death_date = \n| College = [[Duke University|Duke]]\n| Position = [[Center (American football)|Center]]\n| DraftedYear = 1977\n| DraftedRound = 4\n| DraftedPick = 101\n| other_teams,other_years = 1x Second Team All-Pro (1985)\n| ProBowls = \n| DatabaseFootball = BRYANBIL02\n| PFR = \n| playing_years1 = 1977\u20131988\n| playing_team1 = [[Denver Broncos]]\n| CBS = \n}}\n'''Billy Bryan''' , full name William K. Bryan,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://goduke.com/news/2005/12/14/220684.aspx|title=William K. Bryan|website=Duke University|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> (born  June 21, 1955 in [[Burlington, North Carolina]]) is a former American football player in the [[National Football League]]. He was drafted by the [[Denver Broncos]] in the 4th round of the [[1977 NFL Draft]] out of [[Duke University]]. He went on to play for the Broncos from 1977\u20131988 and was [[All-Pro]] in 1985.\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bryan, Bill}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Burlington, North Carolina]]\n[[Category:American football centers]]\n[[Category:Duke Blue Devils football players]]\n[[Category:Denver Broncos players]]\n\n\n{{offensive-lineman-1950s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Emily437", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added an \"Honors and Awards\" section with facts from a source", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billy_Bryan"}
{"title_page": "Bird Claw", "text_new": "{{See also|Claw#Birds}}\n{{Infobox monarch\n| name =Bird Claw\n| title =Ajaw of [[Tikal]]\n| image =Bird Claw.svg\n| image_size =220px\n| caption =Bird Claw's glyph.\n| reign =6th century\n| coronation =\n| full name = \n| predecessor =[[Lady of Tikal]] and<br>[[Kaloomte' Bahlam]]\n| successor =[[Wak Chan K'awiil]]\n| spouse  =\n| issue =\n| royal house =\n| father =\n| mother =\n| birth_date =\n| birth_place =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| date of burial =\n| place of burial =\n| religion =[[Maya religion]] \n|}}\n'''Bird Claw''',<ref group=\"N\">The ruler's name, when transcribed is '''?-TE'?''', Martin & Grube 2008, p.38.</ref> also known as '''Animal Skull I''' and '''Ete I''' (fl. 6th century), was an ''[[ajaw]]'' of the [[Maya civilization|Maya]] city of [[Tikal]]. The monument associated with Bird Claw is Stelae 8.<ref>Martin & Grube 2008, p.38.</ref> He carried a high-ranking name but no Tikal emblem.<ref>Martin & Grube 2008, p.39.</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=\"N\"}}\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin|indent=yes}}<!--BEGIN biblio format. If indent param. is used,  Pls use a colon (:) instead of asterisk (*) for bullet markers in the references list -->\n:{{cite book|author=Martin, Simon|authorlink=Simon Martin (Mayanist)|author2=[[Nikolai Grube]]|year=2008|title=Chronicle of the Maya Kings and Queens: Deciphering the Dynasties of the Ancient Maya|location=London and New York|publisher=[[Thames & Hudson]]|edition=2nd|isbn=9780500287262|oclc=191753193}}\n{{refend}}<!-- END biblio format style -->\n\n{{Clear}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-reg}}\n{{succession box|title=[[Rulers of Tikal|''Ajaw'' of Tikal]]|before=[[Lady of Tikal]] and<br>[[Kaloomte' Bahlam]]|after=[[Wak Chan K'awiil]]|years=6th century}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Tikal}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bird Claw}}\n[[Category:Rulers of Tikal]]\n[[Category:6th century in the Maya civilization]]\n[[Category:6th-century monarchs in North America]]\n\n\n{{